---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Home Loan Interest Rates - Compare All Banks 2026 | TrueCred Loan Expert">

<!-- Page Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span class="sep"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i></span>
        <a href="#">Loans</a>
        <span class="sep"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i></span>
        <span>Home Loan Interest Rates</span>
      </div>
      <h1>Home Loan Interest Rates</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Compare home loan interest rates across all major banks in India for April 2026. Find the lowest rates starting from 8.25% p.a. Both fixed and floating rate options compared. Save lakhs over your loan tenure by choosing the right lender.</p>
      <div class="hero-highlights">
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-percent"></i>
          <span>Lowest Rate: 8.25% p.a.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-building-columns"></i>
          <span>60+ Lenders Compared</span>
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-clock"></i>
          <span>Updated: April 2026</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page Content -->
  <section class="page-content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-grid">

        <!-- Main Content -->
        <div class="content-main">
          <h2>Home Loan Interest Rates in India — April 2026</h2>
          <p>Home loan interest rates in India currently range from 8.25% to 12.50% p.a. across banks and housing finance companies. Most home loans are linked to the bank's external benchmark (repo rate, currently at 6.00%), making them floating rate loans. This means your EMI adjusts when the RBI changes the repo rate. For a ₹50 lakh home loan over 20 years, even a 0.25% rate difference translates to savings of approximately ₹2.5 lakhs over the full tenure.</p>
          <p>TrueCred Loan Expert compares home loan rates from over 60 banks and HFCs including SBI, HDFC Ltd, LIC HFL, ICICI Bank, Bank of Baroda, and PNB Housing. We help you understand the total cost of borrowing — including processing fees, legal charges, insurance, and prepayment terms — not just the headline rate. Our home loan experts also guide you on choosing between fixed and floating rates based on your financial profile and market conditions.</p>

          <div class="info-grid">
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">8.25%</span>
              <span class="info-label">Lowest Rate (p.a.)</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">30 Years</span>
              <span class="info-label">Max Tenure</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">60+</span>
              <span class="info-label">Lenders Compared</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>Home Loan Interest Rate Comparison — April 2026</h3>
          <table class="rate-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Bank / NBFC</th>
                <th>Interest Rate (p.a.)</th>
                <th>Processing Fee</th>
                <th>Max Tenure</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td>SBI</td>
                <td>8.25% - 9.65%</td>
                <td>Up to 0.35%</td>
                <td>30 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>HDFC Ltd</td>
                <td>8.35% - 9.75%</td>
                <td>Up to 0.50%</td>
                <td>30 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>ICICI Bank</td>
                <td>8.40% - 9.85%</td>
                <td>Up to 0.50%</td>
                <td>30 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Bank of Baroda</td>
                <td>8.30% - 10.10%</td>
                <td>Up to 0.50%</td>
                <td>30 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>LIC Housing Finance</td>
                <td>8.35% - 10.25%</td>
                <td>Up to 0.50%</td>
                <td>30 Years</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>

          <h3>Eligibility Criteria</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Indian citizen or NRI aged between 23 and 62 years at loan maturity</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Minimum monthly income of ₹25,000 for salaried applicants</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> CIBIL score of 750+ for best rates; 700+ for standard approval</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Property should be approved by the lending bank and free of legal disputes</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Maximum loan-to-value (LTV) ratio of 80% for loans up to ₹30 lakhs, 75% above</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Stable employment or business income for at least 2-3 years</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>How to Get the Lowest Home Loan Rate</h3>
          <div class="steps-grid">
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">1</div>
              <h4>Check Your Score</h4>
              <p>A CIBIL score of 750+ gets you the best home loan rates. Check your free score on TrueCred before comparing lenders.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">2</div>
              <h4>Compare All Lenders</h4>
              <p>Use our comparison tool to see effective rates (including all charges) from 60+ banks and HFCs side by side.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">3</div>
              <h4>Negotiate & Apply</h4>
              <p>Apply through TrueCred for exclusive rate offers. Our home loan experts negotiate on your behalf for the best possible deal.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">4</div>
              <h4>Track & Close</h4>
              <p>Track your application in real-time. Average processing time is 7-10 days from application to disbursal.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>Documents Required</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Identity Proof — Aadhaar Card, PAN Card, Passport, or Voter ID</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Address Proof — Aadhaar Card, Utility Bill, or Passport</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Income Proof — 6 months salary slips, Form 16, and latest 2 years ITR</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Bank Statements — Last 6-12 months of salary account or business account</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Property Documents — Sale agreement, title deed, builder approvals, and NOCs</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Employment Proof — Offer letter, experience certificate (salaried) or business proof (self-employed)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Sidebar -->
        <div class="content-sidebar">
          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-file-signature"></i> Get Home Loan Rate Quote</h3>
            <form class="sidebar-form" onsubmit="return false;">
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="Full Name" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="tel" class="form-input" placeholder="Mobile Number" maxlength="10" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <select class="form-input" required>
                  <option value="" disabled selected>Loan Amount</option>
                  <option value="1000000">₹10,00,000</option>
                  <option value="2000000">₹20,00,000</option>
                  <option value="3000000">₹30,00,000</option>
                  <option value="5000000">₹50,00,000</option>
                  <option value="7500000">₹75,00,000</option>
                  <option value="10000000">₹1,00,00,000</option>
                  <option value="15000000">₹1,50,00,000</option>
                  <option value="20000000">₹2,00,00,000</option>
                </select>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="City" required>
              </div>
              <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-block" style="width:100%;justify-content:center;">
                Apply Now <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i>
              </button>
            </form>
          </div>

          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-link"></i> Quick Links</h3>
            <div class="sidebar-links">
              <a href="/pages/business-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Business Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/home-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Home Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/loan-against-property"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Loan Against Property</a>
              <a href="/pages/gold-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Gold Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/education-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Education Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/car-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Car Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/credit-cards"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Credit Cards</a>
              <a href="/pages/credit-score"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Credit Score</a>
              <a href="/pages/calculators"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> EMI Calculator</a>
              <a href="/pages/insurance"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Insurance</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-tag">Got Questions?</span>
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <p>Everything you need to know about home loan interest rates.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            Which bank offers the lowest home loan rate in 2026?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              As of April 2026, SBI offers the lowest home loan interest rate starting at 8.25% p.a. for salaried women borrowers under its 'Her Ghar' scheme. For general applicants, SBI starts at 8.40%. Bank of Baroda follows closely at 8.30%, and both HDFC Ltd and LIC HFL start at 8.35%. Actual rates depend on loan amount, property location, and borrower profile.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            Should I choose a fixed or floating home loan rate?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              In the current interest rate environment (repo at 6.00%), floating rate is generally recommended as rates are expected to remain stable or decrease. Floating rates are linked to external benchmarks and adjust immediately when RBI changes rates. Fixed rates offer EMI certainty but are typically 1-2% higher and may have reset clauses. For loans above 10 years, floating rates have historically been more beneficial.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            How much can I save by choosing a lower interest rate?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              On a ₹50 lakh home loan for 20 years, reducing the rate from 9% to 8.25% saves approximately ₹4.7 lakhs in total interest. For a ₹1 crore loan over 25 years, the same 0.75% reduction saves over ₹12 lakhs. Even 0.25% matters in home loans due to the large amounts and long tenures involved.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            Can I switch from fixed to floating rate mid-loan?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Yes, most banks allow conversion from fixed to floating rate (or vice versa) during the loan tenure. A conversion fee of 0.50% to 2% of the outstanding loan amount is typically charged. Alternatively, you can do a home loan balance transfer to another bank offering a lower floating rate. TrueCred helps you evaluate whether conversion or transfer provides better savings.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            How often do home loan rates change?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Since October 2019, home loans are linked to external benchmarks (mostly repo rate). When RBI changes the repo rate, banks must pass on the change within the next quarter. In practice, this means your home loan rate may change 2-4 times per year. You'll receive a notification from your bank, and your EMI or tenure will be adjusted accordingly.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page CTA -->
  <section class="page-content" style="padding-top:0;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="page-cta">
        <div>
          <h3>Find the Best Home Loan Rate for Your Dream Home</h3>
          <p>Compare rates from 60+ banks and HFCs. Save up to ₹12 lakhs on interest over your loan tenure.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="#" class="btn btn-outline" style="color:#fff;border:2px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.5);padding:14px 32px;font-size:0.95rem;">
          Apply Now <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Footer -->

</BaseLayout>
